The paper discusses the application of deep learning to medical image segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of deep learning also involves training and optimization techniques, which are covered in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper specifically focuses on 3D medical images, which could also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for segmentation is a common technique in the neural networks (cs.NE) category.
